<body>

  <header>
    <h1>Fudgy Brownies</h1>
    <p class="note">Delicious Browniee</p>
  </header>

  <h2>Ingredients</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>1/2 cup butter</li>
    <li>1 cup sugar</li>
    <li>2 large eggs</li>
    <li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li>
    <li>1/3 cup cocoa powder</li>
    <li>1/2 cup all-purpose flour</li>
    <li>1/4 teaspoon salt</li>
    <li>1/4 teaspoon baking powder</li>
    <li>1/2 cup chocolate chips</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Instructions</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Preheat your oven to 350°F.</li>
    <li>In a medium saucepan, melt the butter over low heat. Remove from it, stir in sugar, eggs, and vanilla.</li>
    <li>Spread the batter into the prepared pan and smooth the top.</li>
    <li>Sprinkle some choco chips on the batter</li>
    <li>Bake for 20–25 minutes.</li>
    <li>Cool completely in the pan before cutting into squares.</li>
  </ol>

